<br>
1) your guild's reputation is the most important thing you have. Always make sure that your members are aware of that. Their actions not only reflect on themselves, but on the guild. Get a good reputation and people will want to help/join you.<br>
<br>
2) Treat people fairly but firmly. You will find out that some situations will require you to deal with leadership of other guilds. Be respectful, but don't allow yourself to get bullied. Also, don't be afraid to take responsibility for your members actions. if one of your members does something wrong, do your best to make it right, the reverse also applies.<br>
<br>
3) Find good officers. you can't be in game 24/7. They need to act on your behalf. Be open to suggestions and accept criticism.<br>
<br>
4) Lead by example. Have a plan for the guilds progression. Nothing sucks worse than having people level faster than the guild and leaving. You need to have a plan to keep those high level people interested in staying.<br>
<br>
Lastly, realize that you aren't going to make everyone happy. Make your decisions based on what is best for the majority of the guild. If nothing else, people will respect you for it.<br>
<br>
Good Luck!<br>
